h3. Issue Summary

When migrating issues that have sprint history entries, JCMA will insert square brackets on the sprint id(s) list on the cloud database. This will cause some integrations to break due to the way the {{/rest/api/latest/issue/<issue-key>?expand=changelog}} returns the stored values.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a software project in Jira server;
 # Create one sprint and add issues to it;
 # Start the sprint;
 # Create a second sprint;
 # Close the first sprint and move the incomplete issues to the second sprint;
 # Close the second sprint;
 # Use JCMA to migrate the project in which you created the issues and sprints;
 # After migrating to the cloud, run the following endpoint to retrieve the history entries:
 ** 
{code:java}
{{/rest/api/latest/issue/<issue-key>?expand=changelog}}{code}

h3. Expected Results

The sprint id entries should be displayed like the example below:
{code:java}
items": [
          {
            "field": "Sprint",
            "fieldtype": "custom",
            "fieldId": "customfield_<id>",
            "from": "1",
            "fromString": "Sprint 1",
            "to": "1, 2",
            "toString": "Sprint 1,Sprint 2"
          }
        ]{code}
h3. Actual Results

The sprint id entries are displayed within square brackets:
{code:java}
items": [
          {
            "field": "Sprint",
            "fieldtype": "custom",
            "fieldId": "customfield_<id>",
            "from": "[1]",
            "fromString": "Sprint 1",
            "to": "[1, 2]",
            "toString": "Sprint 1,Sprint 2"
          }
        ]{code}
h3. Workaround

Contact Migrations support.

h3. Issue Summary

After a Site import, accessing certain boards resulted in 500 Error. The log show the following:
{code:java}
Caused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Unable to parse QuickFilter JQL
	at com.atlassian.greenhopper.manager.rapidview.QuickFilterManagerImpl.replaceForgottenUsers(QuickFilterManagerImpl.java:359){code}
This is because the table "AO_60DB71_QUICKFILTER" contains value assignee = user@domain.com and is unable to parse assignee.
{code:java}
Unable to parse JQL for QuickFilter [5846] : [assignee in (user@domain.com...
{code}
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create Jira Server board with Quick Filter: assignee = user@domain.com
 # Import site backup of Server into Jira Cloud
 # Access Board with quick filter

h3. Expected Results

Board should be visible
h3. Actual Results
 # 500 Error page

The below exception is thrown:
{noformat}
Caused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Unable to parse QuickFilter JQL
	at com.atlassian.greenhopper.manager.rapidview.QuickFilterManagerImpl.replaceForgottenUsers(QuickFilterManagerImpl.java:359)
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

Atlassian Support needs to execute SQL update on table AO_60DB71_QUICKFILTER to manually enclose assignee value in quotes:
{code:java}
assignee = user@domain.com{code}
Needs to be changed to:
{code:java}
assignee = "user@domain.com"{code}

h3. Issue Summary

Customer migrated one of their Jira cloud instances to another Jira cloud instance. The issue happens in the instance that they have restore the backup from the old instance. So, the app doesn't work in the new instance.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
1- Create a new Jira Cloud instance (we'll call this the old instance)
2- Install Time in Status by OBSS to this instance (https://marketplace.atlassian.com/1211756)
3- Use the Time in Status link in the main Jira menu to open and confirm that Time in Status is working properly.
4- Create a backup of old instance using Backup Manager page (with "Include attachments, avatars, and logos in the backup" selected)
5- Create another Jira Cloud instance (we'll call this the new instance)
6- Restore the backup from the old instance onto the new instance using Restore System page (with "Merge with existing cloud users" selected)
7- Select "grant application access" when restore is completed
8- Install Time in Status to the new instance.
9- Check and confirm that the app is not working on the new instance.

h3. Expected Results

app should work normally
h3. Actual Results

{code:java}
 {"status":500,"message":"An unexpected error has occurred. If this error persists, please contact Time in Status support through http://pluginsupport.obss.com.tr/","messages":["403 : [{\"error\": \"Add-on 'com.obss.plugin.time-in-status' disallowed to impersonate the user because 'no valid active user exists'\"}]"],"pluginVersion":"1.18.0.373","time":"2020-06-08 21:24:48"} {code}

h3. Workaround

After reproducing the same steps that the vendo OBSS did (check the last bounce), we've also received the same error call when trying to access the app in the new instance:
{code:java}
 {"status":500,"message":"An unexpected error has occurred. If this error persists, please contact Time in Status support through http://pluginsupport.obss.com.tr/","messages":["403 : [{\"error\": \"Add-on 'com.obss.plugin.time-in-status' disallowed to impersonate the user because 'no valid active user exists'\"}]"],"pluginVersion":"1.18.0.373","time":"2020-06-08 21:24:48"} {code}
So, we checked the add-on user in the new instance
{code:java}
 select * from cwd_user where email_address like '%time-in-status%' {code}
and saw that the user was appearing as removed:
{code:java}
id,directory_id,user_name,lower_user_name,active,created_date,updated_date,first_name,lower_first_name,last_name,lower_last_name,display_name,lower_display_name,email_address,lower_email_address,credential,deleted_externally,external_id,localservicedeskuser
10009,1,removed10,removed10,1,2020-06-08T20:36:42.632Z,2020-06-08T21:03:36.636Z,,,,,Time in Status,time in status,com.obss.plugin.time-in-status@connect.atlassian.com,com.obss.plugin.time-in-status@connect.atlassian.com,,0,5c988819b709c020b2eee1bc,0{code}

We came into the conclusion that the user was imported as a regular user, not as add-on user, when it was imported in the new instance.
 To confirm, we followed those steps in my instances tests:
 - I uninstalled the app in the new instance
 - I deleted the user:
{code:java}
 delete from cwd_user where id = 14215 {code}

 - I reinstalled the app (it forced the user creation again) and then the app worked

So, I did the same procedure at customer instance and it also worked.
 I checked the user again and now the directory_id=1
{code:java}
 select * from cwd_user where email_address like '%time-in-status%' {code}
{code:java}
id,directory_id,user_name,lower_user_name,active,created_date,updated_date,first_name,lower_first_name,last_name,lower_last_name,display_name,lower_display_name,email_address,lower_email_address,credential,deleted_externally,external_id,localservicedeskuser
